review_content:
@Siv777
The pic here is of the newer, reformulated Coty one (that no longer as the green stem like PI and Unilever had), which was a relatively late development, and could still be bought at drug stores and TJ Maxx as of 4 or 5 years ago. The reformulated version indeed had a darker color to start with, not a sign that it was turned. Compare the bottles in the "fragram" section. It's a consistent feature.

Not that darkening juice is always a sign of a spoiled scent anyway, but here the change is intentional.

@jacig1957 i do not get that much peach in the EDP but a lot of guava, which i guess must be the mirabelle.
I own the EDT and dont get ANY peach in it. But I do get a lot of "guava" on it too, although not as in-your-face- ish. In the EDT it is accompanied by a refreshing lichee and smells waaay less sweet than in the EDP.
So if there is a chance what disturbs you might be the mirabelle and not only the peach, you might not like the EDT too, because it is still very fruity. But it is still a lighter, fresher, more transparent scent than the original.
